def: A man who tills the earth; a husbandman. [Obs.] Tusser.
A cartilaginous lidlike appendage which closes the glottiswhile food or drink is passing while food or drink is passing throughthe pharynx.
One of a series of artificial blue or red dyes obtained fromquinoline and lepidine and used in calico printing.
Noting a flight of stairs, consisting of two or more straightportions connected by a platform (landing) or platforms, and runningin opposite directions without an intervening wellhole.
Opposed to, or checking motion; acting upward; -- applied to aninverted action of the intestinal tube.
One whose occupation is to shear cloth.
To lease again; to grant a new lease of; to let back.
Having a hard texture, as nutshells.
